              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td align="left"><b style="font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: bold; color:#fff; text-shadow: 3px 3px 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5); vertical-align: top; text-transform: uppercase; font-size:27px; line-height:27px;"> CRYOGENIC </b></td>
              </tr>
            </table></td>
          <td valign="top" style="padding-left:15px;"><b style="font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size:18px; color:#006da4; clear:both; display:block; margin-bottom:5px; line-height: 20px;">Temperature Resistant Labels - Cryogenic</b>
            <p style="font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#505050; clear:both; display:block; padding:0; margin:0; line-height:normal; text-align:justify;">As part of this label range we are pleased to announce the introduction of our matt white Polyethylene cryogenic label which can be ordered plain or printed, in roll or sheet formats  and can withstand temperatures down to -196°C. Temperature resistant labels that can withstand very low temperatures are used to label and identify the contents of Polypropylene vials, tubes and storage boxes kept in temperature controlled environments for long periods of time in both vapour and liquid phase, in liquid Nitrogen storage tanks. The adhesive withstands multiple freeze-thaw cycles (reconstitution can be undertaken in ice water, or a warm water bath and samples can be returned to the liquid Nitrogen storage tank). The Polyethylene label face stock is printable via laser and thermal transfer printers. <br />
              <br />
              This material and adhesive are ideal for the labelling of cryogenically stored biological information and samples in various formats and the overprinting of variable data and the amending/updating of information, via conventional hand written means.</p></td>
        </tr>
      </table></td>
