            <p style="font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif; font-size:12px; color:#505050; clear:both; display:block; padding:0; margin:0; line-height:normal; text-align:justify;">An additional label to the range is the matt white Polyethylene heat resistant label which can also be ordered plain or printed, in roll and sheet formats and can withstand temperatures up to 121°C. <br />
              <br />
              The application is for labelling items exposed to heat, such as PCB’s, automotive engine parts and heating systems etc. Along with chemical drum and logistics applications, also due to the exceptional thickness and stability large labels sizes can be used. </p></td>
